Hebeloma aurantioumbrinum

is one of the five most commonly recorded 

Hebeloma

in Greenland with 10.5% of the records considered here. It is common and widely distributed in arctic areas in Europe (
Beker et al. 2016
). From alpine areas, it is known from North America (
Cripps et al. 2019
), but not from the well-investigated alpine mountains in Europe (
Beker et al. 2016
). Circumpolar, arctic-alpine.
